f improvisation. Ultimately, Listening for the Secret is about how the Grateful Dead Phenomenon was possible in the first place, what its social and aesthetic conditions of possibility were, and its results. This is the first book in a new series, Studies in the Grateful Dead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aImprovisation (Music)xSocial aspects. 0aRock musicxSocial aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Rock.2bisacsh  a1970s rock bands.  a20th century rock.  aapolitical band.  acounterculture music.  adeadheads.  afestival music.  agrateful dead society.  agrateful dead.  agreatful dead.  ahistory of the grateful dead.  ahumanities.  aimprov music.  aimprovisational music.  ainfluence of the grateful dead.  ajerry garcia.  alegacy of the grateful dead.  amusic culture.  amusic studies.  amusicians.  aperforming arts.  apolitics of improvisation.  apopular music.  arock band.  arock music.  astudies in music.  athe dead.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052028665840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520961760?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961760/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY